Comment 1: 
I am totally confused by this example,  which uses only foo, bar, Interface, and Struct
(from multiple packages) as names. But I still believe there may be an issue here, so
Accepting it and letting the compiler and spec writers have a look.

Marking "Priority-Soon" so we sort it out.

Meanwhile, can you write an example with less confusing names?
_Labels changed: added **priority-soon**, removed **priority-triage**._ _Status changed to **Accepted**._
